.TH eroosterctl-mailbox-list 1 "June 2026" "eroosterctl" "Erooster Manual"
.SH NAME
eroosterctl\-mailbox\-list \- list mailbox folders for a user
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eroosterctl mailbox list
\fIemail\fR
[\fI\-\-output\fR \fBtable\fR|\fBjson\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Lists all IMAP mailbox folders belonging to the specified user, together with
the number of messages in each folder.
.P
The \fBmailbox\fR command group may be abbreviated as \fBmb\fR:
\fBeroosterctl mb list alice@example.com\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fIemail\fR
Email address of the user (required positional argument).
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fBtable\fR|\fBjson\fR
\fBtable\fR (default) shows two columns: \fBMAILBOX\fR and \fBMESSAGES\fR.
\fBjson\fR emits an array of objects with \fImailbox\fR and \fImessages\fR
fields.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
# Table output
eroosterctl mailbox list alice@example.com

# JSON for a monitoring script
eroosterctl --output json mb list alice@example.com \
  | jq '.[] | select(.messages > 1000)'
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
Success (even if the user has no mailboxes).
.TP
\fB1\fR
Database error or user not found.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBeroosterctl\fR(1),
\fBeroosterctl\-user\-list\fR(1)
